{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b1666aad-8cca-4fe4-97a6-e6b14eb85bf3","content":"Here's what you need to change in your `.csproj`:\n\n**1. Replace packages:**\n\n```xml\n<!-- Remove these -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"NUnit3TestAdapter\" Version=\"4.6.0\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"...\" />\n\n<!-- Add this -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"NUnit.Runner\" Version=\"4.3.0\" />\n```\n\n**2. Enable the new platform in your `<PropertyGroup>`:**\n\n```xml\n<EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatform>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatform>\n```\n\n**3. For `dotnet test` compatibility, also add:**\n\n```xml\n<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n```\n\n**Key notes:**\n- `NUnit.Runner` bundles the Microsoft.Testing.Platform host — no separate SDK package needed.\n- You must be on **NUnit 4.x** (the runner requires it).\n- Your tests can also run as a standalone executable (`dotnet run` or the built `.exe`).\n- `dotnet test` still works when `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` is set.\n\nAfter editing, run `dotnet restore && dotnet test` to verify everything wires up correctly.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"36f56fe1-987d-4da7-907a-78750dcafa16","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing infrastructure migration. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge.\n\nKey changes needed to migrate NUnit from VSTest (NUnit3TestAdapter) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n1. Replace `NUnit3TestAdapter` with `NUnit.Runner` (or the appropriate Microsoft.Testing.Platform adapter for NUnit)\n2. Actually, for NUnit, the migration path involves using `NUnit.Runner` package which integrates with Microsoft.Testing.Platform\n3. Need to add `<EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatform>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatform>` to the project file\n\n\n4. The key issue is that NUnit3TestAdapter doesn't directly support Microsoft.Testing.Platform, so I need to clarify the actual migration approach - either using NUnit.Runner or checking if there's a newer adapter that supports the platform. NUnit.Runner is the package to use for Microsoft.Testing.Platform support, and I need to add the appropriate property to the project file to enable it. I can also remove Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk since that's tied to the older VSTest infrastructure.","outputTokens":1037,"requestId":"E835:1420E8:26B15F4:29277C3:6A0493A6"},"id":"2cc16df4-e8f8-45b0-b34b-a3179811b17c","timestamp":"2026-05-13T15:07:39.825Z","parentId":"2c045a77-0215-4ebd-b22d-06020481497d"}
